President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation on October 27, 2018, to honor the victims of the violent attack at The Tree of Life Synagogue in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on October 31, 2018. The flag will also be flown at half-staff for the same period of time at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.